Berkshire’s Munger Says Greece Hobbled by Work Ethic, Aversion to Taxes

-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 
2011-04-30T16:55:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/berkshire-s-munger-says-greece-hobbled-by-work-ethic-aversion-to-taxes.html
Greece , recipient of a 110 billion-
euro ($163 billion) bailout from the European Union and
 International Monetary Fund , has been hobbled by insufficient
contributions from its citizens,  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A)  Vice
Chairman Charles Munger said today.  “The people don’t want to pay any taxes or do much work,”
Munger said today at Berkshire’s annual meeting in Omaha,
 Nebraska .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Frye in Omaha at 
 afrye@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  